NOTE -  If you re-shape  the bracelet to your wrist,  it cannot be returned.  To learn how to put on a cuff bracelet to avoid bending, please read the following:


About cuffs . . . 

Some people like a tighter fit and some like a looser fit.  But whatever your preference, never bend open a cuff to put it on.  If you open and then squeeze the cuff every  time you put it on or take it off, you will weaken the metal and eventually it will break apart.  

So, how do I put it on?  There is a "soft spot" where the wrist can be squeezed to about  1" thick.  Holding the cuff like a "C" perpendicular to your wrist, push the bottom of the "C" into the soft spot and roll your wrist into the cuff.  To take the bracelet off, just do the reverse.  If you are still not sure, there are many videos on the internet about "how to put on a cuff bracelet".

results.title: Live Laugh Aloha Metal Wall Sign, Hawaiian Decor, Metal Word Sign, Beach Decor, Live Laugh Love, Aloha sign
results.description:
Live Laugh Love metal word sign

Did you love your trip to Hawaii? So did we, which was the inspiration for this sign. While Aloha seems to have a lot of meaning, one is love.  Which is why my wife thought of this phrase for our home.  Great for any room decorating idea to incorporate a little bit of your newly found culture.  Great for hanging over the Hawaii trip photos!

Each one of your signs are made to order in our family shop in Madison Indiana. After you order we will take your personal order and cut it out of a sheet of metal and then grind and prepare it for painting. We then put a super tough powdercoat paint on it and bake it in our oven So that you have the most durable and outdoor or indoor duty sign available. We are a veteran owned and operated family business so we care about you and your order and want you to love it! We love what we do, our product and our customers. 

There are a different options for hanging your sign: 
1.  Use hanging putty tack strips (we use the 3M brand) they are inexpensive and it does not leave any frontward marks on your sign.
2. Use double sided tape.  Just like the hanging putty it is great because it doesn't leave any marks on the front of the sign and gives it a little depth
3. Request to have holes put in your sign and we will drill 1/8" holes in your sign and provide you with 2 nails for your wall at no charge! :-)
You can also read about our hanging instruction in our FAQ and we send hanging instruction with each sign.


All signs are finished in a super tough outdoor duty powdercoat paint in a variety of colors (unless requested bare metal).  What is powder coat you ask?  In a nutshell, it is just the toughest paint available - For more about this see our FAQ about paint. 

All Signs are made to order, but it should not take more than 1-2weeks.
Please contact me if you have questions – We are happy to help you



We do custom orders - just message us and we will work with you on your sign.

All of our products are made to order in Indiana and is proudly veteran owned!
